The paper proposes a new deep RNN architecture for sequential signal reconstruction, specifically for reconstructing video frames from compressive measurements. This task involves both image processing (cs.CV) and optimization (cs.NA) aspects. The proposed network is designed by unfolding the iterations of the proximal gradient method, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the sparsity of signal representations, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
